1. Declare a Doctype -The doctype declaration tells the browser about the HTMl standars you will be using and helps it read and render your markup corrently. 
The <title> tag -- Use meanigful title tags as they help make a web page more meaningful and serach engine friendly. 
Use Descriptve Meta Tags > The description meta attributes describes the basic purpose of the webpage , a summaary of what the web page contains. Use a consice and relevant summary inside the the meta descritption 
Use Dics to Divide your layout into Major sections.  Consider dividing your web page into major sections as the first step in constructing a website design. Doing so from the start promotes clean and well-indented code. It will also help you avoid confusion and excess use of divs, especially if you are writing complex and lengthy markup.
